## POST /api/auth/register

Scenario 1. ACC-001 (email, password, full name required), ACC-002 (email
unique, case-insensitive), ACC-003 (duplicate rejected), ACC-004 (Customer
role, immediately Active, no verification step).

Request:
```json
POST /api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice.nguyen@example.test",
  "password": "correct-horse-battery-staple",
  "fullName": "Alice Nguyen"
}
```

Response — 201 Created:
```json
{
  "id": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-4aaa-8aaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "email": "alice.nguyen@example.test",
  "fullName": "Alice Nguyen",
  "role": "CUSTOMER",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T09:00:00Z"
}
```

Response — 409 Conflict (ACC-003, email already registered; ACC-002 means
this also fires for a case-only difference like `ALICE.NGUYEN@EXAMPLE.TEST`):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "EMAIL_ALREADY_REGISTERED",
    "message": "An account with this email already exists."
  }
}
```

