## POST /api/auth/login

Scenarios 2 (success), 3 (failure).

Request:
```json
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice.nguyen@example.test",
  "password": "correct-horse-battery-staple"
}
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
  "tokenType": "Bearer",
  "expiresIn": 3600
}
```

Response — 401 Unauthorized (ACC-005: wrong password, or an email that
isn't registered at all, or a Deactivated account per ACC-007 — all three
reported with this exact same body, deliberately indistinguishable):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INVALID_CREDENTIALS",
    "message": "Email or password is incorrect."
  }
}
```

---

## Regression check for later phases

Nothing yet to break — this is the first phase. Every phase after this one
must re-verify: register + login still work unchanged, and the 401 body
for a bad login never leaks which of the three ACC-005 causes actually
happened.
